Preconditions:
The input array `nums` must not be null.
The input array `nums` must have at least one element.
The input integer `target` must be a valid value.
The input integer `start` must be a valid index within the range of `nums`.

Postconditions:
The method returns an integer value representing the absolute difference between the index `i` and the input index `start`.
The returned value is always non-negative.